# Backend Requests

## Structure

```
app/
  services/
    campaignService.ts   ← one file per feature/page
  models/
    campaign.ts          ← request/response types for that service
```

- One `*Service.ts` file per feature or page.
- One `*.ts` model file per service — define all request/response types there.
- Never embed `$fetch` or transport details in components or composables directly.

## Service Pattern

Use Nuxt's `$fetch` (auto-imported) for all HTTP calls inside services:

```ts
// app/services/campaignService.ts
import { type Campaign, type CreateCampaignPayload } from "~/models/campaign";

export const fetchCampaigns = () =>
  $fetch<Campaign[]>("/api/campaigns");

export const createCampaign = (payload: CreateCampaignPayload) =>
  $fetch<Campaign>("/api/campaigns", { method: "POST", body: payload });
```

## Composable / Page Usage

Call services from composables, not directly from `<script setup>` in page files:

```ts
// app/composables/useCampaignPage.ts
import { fetchCampaigns } from "~/services/campaignService";

export const useCampaignPage = () => {
  const { data: campaigns, status } = useAsyncData("campaigns", fetchCampaigns);

  return { campaigns, isLoading: computed(() => status.value === "pending") };
};
```

## SSR Safety

- Prefer `useAsyncData` / `useFetch` over raw `$fetch` in composables to get SSR hydration for free.
- Use raw `$fetch` only for mutations (POST/PUT/DELETE) or client-only calls.
- Gate browser-only side effects with `import.meta.client`.
